        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Greetings All...

I just wanted to make a quick post with something that I discovered...

I was on my last 2 blues of 54 and was hunting in The Grey.  The zone started getting seriously overpopulated with players as it's prone to do.  After getting trained on for the 5th time I moved into the Scarlet Desert and came across the Bloodtribes and Lightcrawlers...

There are tons of them heading north from The Grey zone and along the north wall.  Most conned blue at 54 and dubious to me (a DE Necro).  There are three caves along the north wall and I rarely picked up adds when I pulled...

Basically all you need to do is pull up a pet, Augment it and go to work.  Pull with Dooming Darkness (used this one for the quick cast and low mana cost), splurt it, send in the pet and then fear.  Reapply fear and darkness as needed.  Tap it when you start getting low on HP...

I ended up getting a blue an hour and was able to pull non-stop.  Loot is not great (some coin and the occasional emerald ring) but I was really only interested in the exp.  The nice thing about it was there were very few people in zone, I never had competition for mobs, and if I ran into trouble I could zone into Grey (WARNING - MUST HAVE DMF/EB or EB ITEM WHEN ZONING INTO GREY) or Grieg's End.  I dinged 55 and there are still quite a few blues...

Just thought I'd post an easy alternative if you're ever in need of a quite zone to fear kite...

Vorzoth Soulstealer
55 Dark Elf Necromancer
Coinfist Guild High Council
(www.coinfist.com)
Innoruuk Server

Edited by - Vorzoth on 07/08/2002  11:05:31
[/quote]</textarea><br>
